# Project structure

- **Top-level layout**
  - `minecraftmod/` is the Gradle root for this mod (`settings.gradle` includes all subprojects).
  - **mcmod** — platform-neutral foundation: DSLs, abstractions, and shared utilities (no Forge/Fabric or Minecraft runtime deps).
  - **ac** — platform-neutral game logic and content; depends on `mcmod`.
  - **forge-1.20.1** and **fabric-1.20.1** — loader-specific adapters, entrypoints, and resources.

- **mcmod (foundation)**
  - Code lives under `mcmod/src/main/clojure/my_mod/...` with `my-mod.*` namespaces.
  - Domain folders: `block` (dsl, tile_dsl, tile_logic), `client` (obj, render), `events`, `gui` (api, cgui, container, core, dsl, network, etc.), `inventory`, `item` (dsl), `nbt` (dsl), `network`, `platform` (item, nbt, position, resource, world), `registry`, `util`.
  - Stays platform-neutral: no direct Forge/Fabric or Minecraft API imports; only Clojure and data libs.
  - No `src/main/resources` in this module (per `build.gradle`).

- **ac (game content)**
  - Code under `ac/src/main/clojure/my_mod/...` with `my-mod.*` namespaces.
  - Domain folders: `block`, `client/render`, `config`, `energy`, `gui`, `item`, `registry`, `wireless` (network, gui, world data, etc.).
  - Depends on `mcmod`; keeps logic platform-neutral and uses metadata/DSLs from mcmod.
  - Shared assets and data go under `ac/src/main/resources` (e.g. `assets/my_mod/`, `data/my_mod/`).

- **Platform modules (forge-1.20.1, fabric-1.20.1)**
  - `src/main/java` — Java entrypoints and any Java-only integration for the loader.
  - `src/main/clojure/my_mod/forge1201` and `src/main/clojure/my_mod/fabric1201` — adapter namespaces that:
    - Translate loader events into calls into `my-mod.*` (mcmod and ac).
    - Read metadata/DSL from ac/mcmod instead of hardcoding registry names or content IDs.
  - Loader-specific assets and metadata (e.g. `mods.toml`, `fabric.mod.json`, loader-specific lang/models) live in each module’s `src/main/resources`.

- **Adding new content**
  - Add or extend DSL/metadata in **mcmod** for new abstractions (blocks, items, GUIs, etc.).
  - Implement game content in **ac** (new blocks, items, GUIs, energy, wireless, etc.) using mcmod’s DSLs.
  - Touch **forge** or **fabric** only when a feature needs loader-specific glue; then add or extend metadata in ac/mcmod and keep adapter code minimal in the platform module.
